examples: Turn this artwork into a realistic image
prompt.description: The text prompt to generate an image from.
prompt.title: Prompt

num_images.description: The number of images to generate.
num_images.title: Num Images

image_size.description: The desired size of the generated image. If auto, image size will be determined by the model.
image_size.title: Image Size

output_format.description: The format of the generated image.
output_format.title: Output Format

sync_mode.description: If `True`, the media will be returned as a data URI and the output data won't be available in the request history.
sync_mode.title: Sync Mode

enable_safety_checker.description: If set to true, the safety checker will be enabled.
enable_safety_checker.title: Enable Safety Checker

seed.description: Random seed for reproducible results. If None, a random seed is used.
seed.title: Seed

image_urls.description: The URLs of the images to use as a reference for the generation. A maximum of 2 images are supported.
image_urls.title: Image Urls

guidance_scale.description: Controls how much the model adheres to the prompt. Higher values mean stricter adherence.
guidance_scale.title: Guidance Scale

images.description: A list of the generated images.
images.title: Images

seed.description: The base seed used for the generation process.
seed.title: Seed

file_size.description: The size of the file in bytes.
